The paper discusses the use of gradients in machine learning models, specifically in deep networks for object recognition, virtual screening, and language modeling. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). However, given the focus on deep networks and feature importance, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.CR.
